snippet.textDisplay:
I always found it funny how the Fresno Air Terminal tried to officially change its name to the Fresno-Yosemite International Airport, so instead of FAT, they'd have FYI. The local news called it by the new name, but obviously they are stuck with the old call letters.

At least the local bus service got to be Fresno Area eXpress (FAX). I hear they were inspired by the BART, which would have left Fresno with a FAT FART for their transportation systems.

They also tried offering free to borrow bicycles within the city to try helping low income people get around town. The point being go where you need, then leave the bike for the next person. Pretty sure the bikes were stolen, because I never saw these yellow bikes, or heard about the program after its initial launch.

It's also the largest city in the USA to not have an Interstate Highway. It needs it.

Those and many more reasons are why Fresno sucks.
